radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys. No bile duct dilatation or gallbladder abnormalities. Normal mucosal pattern of the jejunum and ileum. No obstructing lesion in the colon. Normal appendix with air inside and no signs of appendicitis. Area of stranding with focal encapsulated fat in the left lower quadrant consistent with epiploic appendagitis. Small amount of free fluid in the rectovescical pouch.
